<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-01-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-01-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="650" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d650">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Taylor</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-01-10"><hi rend="italic">January 10,
                                1895</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>No. Arrangement has been made strictly according to the terms of your
                            telegrams. Upon that basis Cortes will be asked to give favored-nation
                            treatment to American products immediately. Tariff changes may be made
                            by both nations without prejudice, provided neither discriminates
                            against other. If either resolves to discriminate, three months’ notice
                            to be given. Details by next mail.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>